ed geographies of popular power that endure to the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCooperationzItalyxHistory. 0aCooperative societieszItalyxHistory. 0aFraternal organizationszItalyxHistory. 0aLocal governmentzItalyxHistory. 0aMunicipal governmentzItalyxHistory. 0aSocialismzItalyxHistory. 4aPhilosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173174740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501731747423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501731747/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles